<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-25T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1981: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-25T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                        1928—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>169. Your 303, August 7, 10 a.m., and Department’s 163, August 14, 7 p.m.
                            The bankers have now definitely decided that they do not wish to submit
                            a copy of the draft Financial Plan to President Diaz at the present
                            time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>